 f(z)=\exp z=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}a_n (z-\pi i)^n.~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~(1) 
 g(z)=f(z-\pi i)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}a_n(z-\pi i)^n.~~~~~~~~~~~~~(2) 
 g(z)=f(z-\pi i)=\exp(z-\pi i)=-\exp z=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n!}(z-\pi i)^n\\\Leftrightarrow\exp z=-\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n!}(z-\pi i)^n 
 a_n=-\frac{1}{n!}. 
z\leftarrow z-\mathrm i\pi.
\exp z=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\dfrac{1}{n!} z^n
-\exp z=\exp z\,\exp(-\mathrm i\pi)=\exp(z-\mathrm i\pi)=\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\dfrac{1}{n!} (z-\mathrm i\pi)^n.
\exp z=-\sum_{n=0}^{\infty}\dfrac{1}{n!} (z-\mathrm i\pi)^n.
